---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";import FantasyHeader from "../../components/FantasyHeader.astro";import FantasyDisclaimer from "../../components/FantasyDisclaimer.astro";import { fantasyPlayers, averageFixtureDifficulty } from "../../data/fantasy";
const watch=fantasyPlayers.filter(p=>p.tags.includes("differential")||p.tags.includes("value")||p.tags.includes("budget")).map(p=>({...p,run:averageFixtureDifficulty(p.clubSlug)})).sort((a,b)=>(b.evidence-b.planningPrice*2)-(a.evidence-a.planningPrice*2));
---
<Base title="Fantasy Football Differentials & Value Watchlist 2026/27" description="An independent 2026/27 fantasy football watchlist for value, lower-cost and under-the-radar players, with fixtures and minutes risks clearly labelled." canonical="/fantasy-football/differentials/">
  <FantasyHeader/><div class="fantasy-page"><div class="fantasy-tool-hero"><div class="fantasy-container"><nav class="fantasy-breadcrumbs"><a href="/fantasy-football/">Fantasy</a><span>/</span><span>Differentials</span></nav><span class="fantasy-eyebrow">Not an ownership claim</span><h1>Look beyond the obvious names.</h1><p>Our differential label means editorially under-the-radar or lower-cost—it does not claim a live ownership percentage. Add candidates to a private browser watchlist and review them through pre-season.</p></div></div><section class="fantasy-section"><div class="fantasy-container"><div class="ranking-list">{watch.map((p,i)=><article class="ranking-card"><b>{i+1}</b><div><strong>{p.name}</strong><span>{p.club} · {p.position} · {p.planningPrice.toFixed(1)} credits · opening difficulty {p.run.toFixed(1)}<br/>{p.note}</span></div><button class="fantasy-button fantasy-button--dark" style="min-height:36px;padding:.5rem .65rem" data-watch={p.id} data-name={p.name}>Watch</button></article>)}</div><FantasyDisclaimer/></div></section></div>
  <script is:inline>const key="lastseason-fantasy-watchlist";const read=()=>{try{return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(key)||"[]")}catch{return[]}};const sync=()=>{const saved=read();document.querySelectorAll("[data-watch]").forEach(b=>b.textContent=saved.some(x=>x.id===b.dataset.watch)?"Watching":"Watch")};document.querySelectorAll("[data-watch]").forEach(b=>b.addEventListener("click",()=>{const saved=read(),exists=saved.some(x=>x.id===b.dataset.watch),next=exists?saved.filter(x=>x.id!==b.dataset.watch):[...saved,{id:b.dataset.watch,name:b.dataset.name}];localStorage.setItem(key,JSON.stringify(next));sync()}));sync();</script>
</Base>
